questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where migrating a high-throughput Spring Boot application to Java 21 Virtual Threads led to severe thread starvation and application freezing under heavy database load. A thread dump reveals that many Virtual Threads are in the `PARKED` state, while carrier platform threads are blocked. The following code pattern is used for executing queries:

java
public class QueryExecutor {
    private final Object lock = new Object();

    public List<Result> executeQuery(String query) {
        synchronized (lock) {
            // Calls blocking legacy JDBC driver
            return databaseConnection.run(query);
        }
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where a developer attempted to parallelize database writes using `CompletableFuture` inside a Spring `@Transactional` service block:

java
@Service
public class OrderService {
    @Transactional
    public void processOrder(Order order) {
        CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
            paymentRepository.save(order.getPayment());
        });
        orderRepository.save(order);
    }
}

During peak traffic, payment transactions fail to save or bypass the transaction lifecycle of the service method entirely, leaving inconsistent records in the database.

You are debugging a production issue where an asynchronous data enrichment pipeline silently swallows failures. When a downstream HTTP call fails, no errors are logged, and the execution chain halts silently without notifying the parent monitoring system:

java
public CompletableFuture<Void> processAsync(Request request) {
    return CompletableFuture.supplyAsync(() -> fetchUserData(request))
            .thenApply(user -> enrichData(user))
            .thenAccept(enriched -> saveToDatabase(enriched));
}
